import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(data=data, x='year', y='count', hue='job', legend='full')
    plt.title('What is the trend of job distribution across different occupations over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(loc='upper left', bbox_to_anchor=(1, 1))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(15, 6))
    chart = sns.barplot(x='job', y='count', data=data, ci=None)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of job count across different occupations?', wrap=True)
    chart.legend(title='Occupations', loc='upper right', labels=data['job'].unique())

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_gender = data.groupby('sex')['count'].sum().reset_index()
    plt.pie(data_gender['count'], labels=data_gender['sex'], autopct='%.2f%%')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of job count across different genders?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(data_gender['sex'], loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='perc', hue='sex', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of job distribution for men and women over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Percentage of Job Distribution')
    plt.legend(title='Gender')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='perc', bins=30, kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['perc'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['perc'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Percentage of Individuals in Occupation')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('Distribution of Percentage of Individuals in the Occupation Relative to the Total Population', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
